>>889236579
Having a kid isn't "something you do", it's a permanent fundamental change to almost every aspect of your life. We have a 4 and 6 year old, and every day is a new challenge. It's absolutely exhausting, kids are irrational assholes a lot of the time, and if you intend to commit to it, it will often feel as though you're living for them and not yourself.

I used to think I was a patient person, but before I had kids I don't think I really knew what patience was. They will test you in ways you would never be tested if you didn't have kids, and in ways that you cannot yet conceive of.

I suspect that once they get a little older the amount of time and effort you have to dedicate to your kids might diminish somewhat, but we're not there yet.

The days are long but the years are short. Proceed with both eyes open, it will certainly be the greatest challenge of your life, and perhaps the greatest payoff, in the sense that you are creating humans who might effect positive outcomes in the lives of others, or in the rare case the world at large.
